## 4. HONEST STUBS AND DISCLOSURES

Per plan.md, the cover letter and one-pager both include an explicit disclosure that
the demo does not literally stream a 500 MB file in a browser tab (server-side work,
not safe in a browser). The exact phrasing:

  "One honest note on the demo: it does not literally stream 500 MB inside a browser
  tab, because that is server work and a browser cannot do it safely. It runs the real
  algorithm on smaller SAF-T fixtures and visualizes the memory behavior at scale. That
  is deliberate. It shows you the exact approach the Milestone 2 proof of concept will
  prove on real files, before you have spent a euro."

This is a brand-voice signal (honest, candid, "Story with stakes") and also a trust
mechanism: a client who notices the limitation will find it already acknowledged.

