## 8. NOTES FOR NEXT RUNS

- The lxml.iterparse Q1 answer (elem.clear() + ancestor pruning, 80-120 MB vs 600-800 MB)
  is factually grounded. Keep this as the standing template for any large-file parsing
  posting answer.
- The four-layer tenant isolation Q2 answer (JWT, SQLAlchemy tenant scope, PostgreSQL RLS,
  API tests) with the PgBouncer SET LOCAL caveat is a reliable technical differentiator.
  Reuse and adapt for any multi-tenant SaaS posting.
- The "honest stub" disclosure pattern (acknowledge the demo's limitation proactively)
  performed well in the evaluator's trust-signal assessment. Use it whenever a demo
  genuinely cannot replicate a server-side capability.
- EU timezone preference was addressed ("I work EU-friendly hours") without falsely
  claiming EU residency. This phrasing is safe to reuse.

